    "uen": "53449563W",
    "description": "<p>At Huckleberry, our team strive to deliver high quality music lessons with strong emphasis on techniques such as sight reading, aural ability, music interpretation, appreciation and more. It is our belief that when well guided, student will develop a natural curiosity and discipline in their learning behaviour and subject of interest.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>We strongly encourage students to participate in our annual recitals, music festivals, piano competitions and masterclasses to gain confidence in music handling. A good grading in the music exam is a product of these exposures, which students and parents can decide on their participation.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Huckleberry students will be offered the opportunity to participate in ensemble and duet playing and also as an accompaniment to another instrument. The Huckleberry teaching team hopes to give students from all walks of life an exposure to a rigourous music training ground, and hopefully, be able to enjoy and appreciate music at a higher level in the next stage of their life endeavours.</p>",
